<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="<%= language === 'zh' ? 'zh-TW' : 'en' %>">
<head>
<!-- meta attributes -->
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="author" content="Jack Gowan">
<meta name="description" content="first built maze">
<title>The Maze - Ignore the Statue</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/a_maze_style.css">
</head>
<body>
<h1 class="main-title">You press forward</h1>

  <div class="room-container">
    <div class="content-wrapper">
      <div class="room-image">
        <img src="/images/a2_maze-ignore-statue.png" alt="Pressing forward past the statue">
      </div>
      <div class="room-content">
        <div class="room-text">
          <code>
            You decide the statue is a distraction. The insect noises behind those doors are growing louder and more agitated. Best to keep moving.
            <p>You hurry past the glowing statue and down a narrow corridor. The light fades behind you as you descend deeper into the maze.</p>
            <p> Going carefully along the tunnels you patiently search out any traps, you journey along one corridor and then another. </p>
            <p> You see a bridge, broken in the middle, it looks far too risky to jump across.</p> 
            <p>You go up a flight of stairs.</p>
            code>
        </div>

        <hr/>

        <div class="navigation">
          <p><%= translations?.[language]?.choices?.prompt || 'Your only path in the maze is up the staircase:' %></p>
          <a href="/maze/hide-stairs"><%= translations?.[language]?.choices?.options?.[0] || 'Cautiously you move up the staircase' %></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    // Detect back button and redirect to start
    window.onpageshow = function(event) {
      if (event.persisted || (performance.navigation && performance.navigation.type === 2)) {
        window.location.replace('/');
      }
    };
  </script>
</body>
</html>
